Class MMTransformer

java.lang.Object
  lu.uni.geko.common.AbstractModelTransformer<Pair<org.eclipse.emf.common.util.URI,org.eclipse.emf.common.util.URI>>
      lu.uni.geko.mmtransformer.MMTransformer

public class MMTransformer
extends AbstractModelTransformer<Pair<org.eclipse.emf.common.util.URI,org.eclipse.emf.common.util.URI>>

A metamodel transformer that makes base metamodels suitable for weaving (if necessary) and derives an advice and pointcut metamodel from it.

createMMPackage

private org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EPackage createMMPackage(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EPackage originalPackage,
                                                       String newName,
                                                       String newNsPrefix,
                                                       String newNsURI,
                                                       String containerName)
Creates a root package of a new metamodel that is derived from the given root package of a metamodel. The name, the namespace prefix and the namespace URI of the new package are set according to the parameters and a new container metaclass bearing the given name is introduced.

Parameters:
originalPackage - the root package of a metamodel
newName - the name for the root package of the new metamodel
newNsPrefix - the namespace prefix for the root package of the new metamodel
newNsURI - the namespace URI for the root package of the new metamodel
containerName - the name for the container metaclass that is introduced into the new metamodel
Returns:
the root package of the derived metamodel

generateAndModifyGenModel

private org.eclipse.emf.codegen.ecore.genmodel.GenModel generateAndModifyGenModel(org.eclipse.emf.common.util.URI mmURI,
                                                                                  String pluginsDirAndIDAppendage,
                                                                                  org.eclipse.emf.common.util.Monitor monitor)
Generates and modifies a generator model for generating code for the metamodel at the given URI and returns it. First, the parameter pluginsDirAndIDAppendage is appended to the default IDs and directories of the plug-ins that can be generated using this generator model. Second, the generator models is modified by executing all installed extensions for the corresponding extension point.

Parameters:
mmURI - the URI of a metamodel
pluginsDirAndIDAppendage - the string to be appended to the default plug-in directory and ID
monitor - the monitor to be used for logging output during code generation
Returns:
the generator model used for code generation

Parameters:

genModel - a generator model used for code generation

calculateNewPluginIDOrDir

private String calculateNewPluginIDOrDir(String keptAppendage,
                                         String pluginIDOrDir,
                                         String pluginsDirAndIDAppendage,
                                         String modelCodePluginDirAndIDAppendage)
Calculates a new plug-in IDs or directory of a plug-ins by inserting a new appendage between the original ID or directory and the default appendage. Removes the given modelCodePluginDirAndIDAppendage that was wrongly added by EMF to all plug-in IDs and directories (and not only to the ID and directory of the model plug-in).

Parameters:
keptAppendage - the default appendage to be kept
pluginIDOrDir - the default plug-in ID or directory
pluginsDirAndIDAppendage - the string to be appended to the default plug-in directory and ID
modelCodePluginDirAndIDAppendage - the appendage from the model code plug-in to be removed
Returns:
the new plug-in ID or directory

generateModelEditAndEditorCode

private void generateModelEditAndEditorCode(org.eclipse.emf.codegen.ecore.genmodel.GenModel genModel,
                                            org.eclipse.emf.common.util.Monitor monitor,
                                            boolean onlyModelCode)
Generates model edit and editor code using the given generator model and monitor. Edit and editor code are only generated if onlyModelCode is false.

Parameters:
genModel - the generator model
monitor - the monitor to be used for logging output
onlyModelCode - whether to generate only model or also edit and editor code
